1. Ensure AWS credentials are configured (`aws configure`) with an account that can create resources.
2. From terraform folder:

terraform init
terraform apply -var="key_pair_name=YOUR_KEY" -var="ssh_cidr=YOUR.IP.32" -var="bucket_name=unique-bucket-name"
# if you don't want to provide key pair and want to use SSM instead set key_pair_name=""

3. Test HTTP server:

curl $(terraform output -raw ec2_http_url)

4. Run Python verification:

pip install boto3
python python/s3_check_secure.py $(terraform -chdir=terraform output -raw s3_bucket_name)

5. Cleanup:

terraform -chdir=terraform destroy -auto-approve
